<h1 class="bac"><%=program.Item("title")%></h1>

<div class="expanded">
<% call expandableH2("our_business", true) %>
<div>
<p class="bac nobr">Global Commercial Banking (GCB) is one of the largest commercial banks in the U.S., serving companies with revenues of $1 million to more than $2 billion through our core businesses:</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Middle Market
		<ul class="secondary m15">
			<li>Dealer Financial Services</li>
			<li>Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America Business Capital</li>
		</ul>
	</li>
	<li>Business Banking</li>
	<li>Client Development Group</li>
	<li>Commercial Real Estate Banking</li>
	<li>Specialized Industries</li>
	<li>Credit Products</li>
	<li>Treasury Solutions</li>
	<li>Enterprise Client Coverage</li>
</ul>
<p class="bac">Our unique client coverage model and close partnerships with other lines of business, such as Global Banking and Markets, Global Wealth and Investment Management and Consumer &amp; Small Business Banking, enable our commercial client teams to seamlessly deliver all of the bank&#39;s capabilities as integrated solutions.</p>
<p class="bac">Treasury Solutions partners with GCB client management groups (Middle Market Banking, Business Banking, Commercial Real Estate Banking, Specialized Industries, Client Development Group and Dealer Financial Services) to provide expertise, experience and products that help clients maximize their working capital and achieve their goals. Treasury Solutions also partners closely with Global Treasury Sales, Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America Merchant Services and Service and Fulfillment to deliver the full capabilities of the enterprise to our clients.</p>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<% call expandableH2("overview", false) %>
<div>
<p class="bac">The program is designed to build strong talent for various positions within Global Commercial Banking. The program emphasizes on-the-job training augmented by classroom instruction focused on technical, analytical and professional skills.</p>
<p class="bac">Program analysts receive both on the job training and instructor led training to gain broad exposure and understanding of a key functional area within Global Commercial Banking.  The program provides exposure to treasury with an intensive focus on how to best deliver innovative solutions to our clients. As a member of the Analyst Program, you will have exposure to members of the leadership team and the opportunity to interact with our clients.</p>
<p class="bac nobr">Upon completion of the program, participants will:</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Understand and clearly articulate Treasury Management client needs and product profitability</li>
	<li>Exhibit knowledge of sales analytics, pricing models and product markets across the Treasury franchise</li>
	<li>Demonstrate understanding of the Middle Markets segments and the variables that drive revenue and impact client profitability</li>
	<li>Understand how a deal moves through the treasury pipeline</li>
	<li>Demonstrate understanding of the Treasury Management industry, both domestic and international</li>
	<li>Demonstrate knowledge of key product set, including the common variations and their applicability</li>
</ul>
</div></div>
<div class="expand">
<% call expandableH2("qualifications", false) %>
<div>
<p class="bac">Candidates must have a bachelor&#39;s degree with a minimum of six (6) credit hours of finance and/or accounting. Candidates must have a demonstrated record of achievement, such as extracurricular activities or leadership roles. Some common driving characteristics include: finance knowledge, excellent verbal and written communication skills, personal leadership, the ability to inspire a strong sense of camaraderie and technical skills such as Excel and PowerPoint and strong time management skills.</p>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<% call expandableH2("training", false) %>
<div>
<p class="bac">Virtual, web-based and instructor-led learning solutions are used to supplement the experiential development that occurs on-the-job. Throughout the program, analysts are provided a support network, which consists of the program manager, rotation managers and mentors. Important parts of this network are former college program analysts.  You will also complete trainings on the various bank systems we offer and are required for the role.</p>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<% call expandableH2("locations", false) %>
<div>
<p class="bac">Please check career website for specific location. Geographic flexibility is required at the end of the program in an effort to fill business-critical roles.</p>
</div></div>

